This folder contains screenshots demonstrating vulnerability findings before remediation and validation results after applying STIG remediation scripts.

Each subfolder represents a phase of the remediation process:
- Initial scan
- Identified findings
- Remediation execution
- Validation scan
- Post-remediation results

Notes:
- The WinVerifyTrust finding required remediation across both 64-bit and 32-bit registry paths.
  Initial remediation did not resolve the issue until both paths were configured and the system was rebooted.
- Print Spooler was disabled as it was not required in the lab environment. In production environments, this control    
  should be evaluated based on business requirements.
- WN11-00-000065 – Disable Guest Account: 
    Detection Method:
    - Validated locally using PowerShell (Get-LocalUser).
    - Guest account was enabled in a lab environment to simulate a misconfiguration and demonstrate remediation.
- Password policy settings were validated and enforced using local account policy commands. 
- Maximum password age was configured to align with STIG requirements.
- Account lockout policies were configured to mitigate brute-force attacks by enforcing lockout thresholds and durations in accordance with STIG guidelines.
